Module 31 – The Archive Is the Appeal 📂📜

Core Message

When courts won’t hear your appeal, the public record can.

⸻

Lesson Introduction

Publishing filings, procedural histories, and rulings can create a parallel form of review — one that influences future cases, public opinion, and policy.

⸻

Teaching Block

1. Archive Completely
	•	Include all filings, exhibits, and procedural notes.

2. Organize for Accessibility
	•	Public repositories, indexed for search.

3. Frame as Legal Memory
	•	Your archive becomes precedent in the court of public opinion.

⸻

Real-World Illustration

The Legal Calculus archive preserved filings from vanished PACER entries, ensuring they remained accessible to other litigants.

⸻

Assignment Prompt

Task:
List two platforms where you could publish a case archive.

⸻

Model Answer (Sample)
	1.	GitHub Pages
	2.	Public Google Drive folder

⸻

Reflection Summary

If the appeal is blocked, the archive keeps the fight alive.

⸻

Visual Pairing

Image Concept:
A courthouse morphing into a public library. Caption:
“Preserve It Where They Can’t Erase It.”